<TITLE> WFP gets new chief for Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 6 (bdnews24.com)  John Aylieff has taken over as the World Food Programme representative in Bangladesh, WFP said in a statement Sunday. Aylieff, who had earlier worked in the humanitarian and development sector, served as emergency coordinator and director for the Assessment, Analysis and Preparedness Division of WFP Headquarters in Rome, Italy. He managed WFP's largest special operation, aimed at providing logistics support to the delivery and monitoring of food across Iraq in 2003 while working at Larnaca, Cyprus. Aylieff served WFP's Brussels office as director of the European Commission Relations Division from 2003 to 2006. "I am delighted to have been appointed to serve in Bangladesh," Aylieff said on his new appointment. bd
